        <b>
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:
  18.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Weights and Measures Department sealed filing stations in FCT.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
  normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;
  mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">
        <o:p>
                    &nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
  normal">
<span 
                        lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;
  mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  text-align:justify;line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:
  small; font-family:Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">The Weights and Measures Department of the Federal Ministry of Trade 
                    and Investment had sealed dispensing pumps of AYM Shafa filling station at Gudu 
                    district, M. Major Oil and Gas, Mbora and NNPC Mega station at Gwarinpa for 
                    under dispensing petroleum products to customers.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:small; font-family:
  Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">This was discovered during the inspection of filing stations carried 
                    out by the Weights and Measures Department led by its Director, Alhaji Bashir 
                    Zoro in Abuja.<o:p></o:p><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;
  mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-no-proof:
  yes"><img alt="FIINGSTATION" height="225" align="left"
                        src="images/fillinstation.jpg" 
                        v:shapes="Picture_x0020_5" width="300" /></span></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:small; font-family:
  Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">During the inspection at the AYM, Shafa filing station, Gudu District, 
                    it was discovered that the dispensing pumps at the station short-changed 0.8 
                    litres for every 20 litres of PMS (19.2 as 20 litres) and Diesel 0.95 litres 
                    less for every 20 litres (19.05 as 20 litres); at the M. Major Oil and Gas 
                    Mbora, 1.6 litres for every 20 litres (18.4 as 20 litres).<o:p></o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:small; font-family:
  Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">The NNPC Mega station, Gwarinpa created a drama on sighting the 
                    Weights and Measures officials.&nbsp; They called their sales attendant to hide 
                    from the team before the team could disembark from their vehicle when it was 
                    obvious that they were dispensing PMS to customers on a long queue before the 
                    arrival of the Weights and Measures officials.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:small; font-family:
  Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">The officials of the filing station refused to switch on their 
                    dispensing pumps and started making excuses on power supply and they refused to 
                    put on their generator and when&nbsp; the waiting game continued for a while&nbsp; 
                    and they were not forthcoming, the Director ordered the sealing of the 
                    dispensing pumps at the filing station.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:small; font-family:
  Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Director, Weights and Measures, Alhaji Bashir Zoro while addressing 
                    journalists at the NNPC Mega station said that it was extremely disappointing 
                    that motorists were being short changed at the filing stations and that&nbsp; 
                    the Department&nbsp; will continue to embark on such exercise&nbsp; in order to 
                    establish that marketers&nbsp; conform with fairness and standards.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:small; font-family:
  Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">He said that the objective of the inspection was to checkmate 
                    unscrupulous businessmen from unfair trade practices and safeguard the interest 
                    of consumers and producers alike.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:small; font-family:
  Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">In his words, “It is extremely disappointing that motorists are being 
                    short changed, we would not relent in our official duty to ensure that marketers 
                    conform with integrity, fairness and accuracy in dispensing PMS to customers.&nbsp; 
                    We shall continue to use the media to educate marketers and the general public 
                    so that they would be alert to the need to become conscious of measurement and 
                    standards as the law prescribed.”<o:p></o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:small; font-family:
  Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Other filing stations inspected by the team were AP filing station, 
                    Apo, Oando at Gaduwa and Jabi respectively and they were requested to come with 
                    their verification certificate while OandoJabi dispensing pumps were found to be 
                    accurate and fair.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
  line-height:normal">
        <span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:small; font-family:
  Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">The verification certificate is mandatory for every marketer to 
                    possess for its equipment which is valid for a year and it is usually issued 
                    after dispensing pumps had been tested and found to be accurate but due to their 
                    nature and in a bid to maximize profit some marketers do readjust their meter to 
                    short-change motorists.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
